# The requirement's own value at every state, for a run trace to draw.
#
# A companion function evaluates the same node the verdict comes from, at a
# state the caller picks, so the column is the same compiler on the same AST
# -- there is no second evaluator to disagree with the verdict. referee checks
# that the column's first-state value equals the verdict on every explain run;
# a mismatch is a bug in referee, not a picture.

data a : integer;

# A temporal requirement: false at a state is a claim about the suffix from
# there, so its row is drawn as a span, not a cell. Marked `temporal`.
@always_nonneg
G(a >= 0);

# A state requirement: false at a state is a fact about that state. Marked
# `state`, and the distinction is the reason a plotting library is the right
# viewer rather than a waveform one.
@a_is_one_here
a == 1;
